cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision tasks, specifically video object segmentation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces a novel two-stream neural network with an explicit memory module, which involves learning from data and could fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper uses convolutional gated recurrent units to implement the visual memory, which could be considered a form of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also evaluates its method on two motion segmentation datasets, which could fall under the category of multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper uses a small number of training video sequences to learn the visual memory, which could involve some form of optimization or neural network training, and therefore could also fall under the category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
